        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/loren_sonkin/{size}/382_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-12-22T14:17:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nice.  I just had this last week and your bottle was better than mine.  Mine was old and way past peak  I scored it 82.  Though those who like old wines liked it better than I.  Fwiw, my note is here:  <a href=\"https://www.intowine.com/reviews/1979-ch%C3%A2teau-mouton-rothschild-france-bordeaux-pauillac-wine-review\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://www.intowine.com/reviews/1979-ch\u00e2teau-mouton-rothschild-france-bordeaux-pauillac-wine-review</a></p>\n<p>Of course, at that age, every bottle is different.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\"></p>",
